Knowing you, I believe it! The icicles on your steel jock strap must have been *really* embarrassing. I'm really surprised you did not use your solar powered plutonium reserve entropy distorting GI issue steel jock strap heater! Everyone else had one!<br><br>
And you thought you were a really big man, huh! ;)<br><br>
We used to catch rides on 8&quot; rounds. Just flip the old steel jock strap over the nose as it emerged from the tube, hang on, and you were in the next province before you knew it! 175mm high angle was a really good ride to 40,000 feet or so. We sold the &quot;Stars and Stripes&quot; and beer cockpit to cockpit to those bored flyboys on the way by. Made a little money for R&amp;R that way. You won't admit it, but you were in our frequent customer club, weren't you! I looked up your handle.<br><br>
And I bet you thought we were fighting the enemy. Heck, no! It was just a big gun bunny jamboree. You fly boys always had an attitude 'till we came whizzing by. Faked you right out.<br><br>
PP-38's were just that.<br><br>
